tldr: "The user requested a review of their sleep questionnaire implementation
  against the provided specification and a plan to address missing features. The
  agent successfully implemented the first three high-priority items from the
  plan: a tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, and insufficient sleep
  syndrome detection."
overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed specification and SOW. The agent performed a
  comprehensive analysis, identifying several gaps and missing features, which
  were then prioritized into a detailed action plan. The agent proceeded to
  implement the first three high-priority items. This involved integrating a
  1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference, complete with safety warnings
  for high scores, into the questionnaire UI and both web and PDF reports.
  Additionally, the agent implemented the detection and reporting of COMISA
  (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, ensuring
  these conditions are accurately identified and communicated in the user's
  personalized report. The implementation involved updating data types,
  validation schemas, and the display logic in both the interactive report
  section and the PDF generation component.
